Chad Arendse (19) was shot and killed in Rocklands on Youth Day after attending a 21st birthday party. CAPE TOWN - Police have arrested a suspect in connection with the fatal shooting of a Mitchell's Plain teenager. Chad Arendse (19) was shot and killed in Rocklands on Youth Day after attending a 21st birthday party. The police's Noloyiso Rwexane said the suspect is expected to appear in court on Monday. "He was arrested on the 11th of July. He is facing a charge of murder." Meanwhile, residents in gang-infested areas wait with bated breath for soldiers to start working on the ground, as part of Police minister Bheki Cele's plan to clamp down on crime.